headline: TE Connectivity announces 9% increase in quarterly cash dividend to $0.71
summary: TE Connectivity plc (NYSE: TEL) announced today that its board of directors declared a regular quarterly cash dividend of $0.71 per ordinary share, payable on June 10, 2025, to shareholders of record at the close of business on May 21, 2025. This payment represents a 9% increase from the $0.65 per ordinary share quarterly dividend paid to shareholders on March 7.

headline: TE Connectivity (NYSE:TEL) Faces Patent Infringement Allegations Involving AEC Technology
summary: TE Connectivity (NYSE:TEL) recently faced a legal complaint from Credo Technology Group concerning alleged patent infringements, which was a notable development affecting the company's share performance. Over the past month, TE Connectivity's stock experienced a 4% decline, aligning with broader market challenges.
